SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1987.tb02554.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT Prior studies indicate that common stocks tend to earn negative returns immediately following listing on the NYSE. The authors document the phenomenon in detail and investigate a number of possible explanations. No full explanation is discovered, although several are ruled out.
ER  - 

